repo.description: Parse and serialize minecraft packets, plus authentication and encryption.
repo.name: node-minecraft-protocol

body:
To support https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/issues/312 WebSockets, a variation of `createClient()` recognizing `options.stream`, set to an arbitrary Node.js Stream. To do:

* [x] createClientStream() moved from wsmc/minecraft-protocol-stream.js, functional parity (working in concert with with https://github.com/deathcap/wsmc/pull/26)
* [x] Refactor createClient() to use createClientStream()
* [x] Test - CircleCI unit tests pass, also works in my own testing with wsmc
* ~~Fix packet framing disabling hack (`noPacketFramer` option, client.framer = EmptyTransformStream, has no `.unpipe()` method - surely there must be a cleaner means to achieve disabling framing)~~ removed in favor of https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/pull/316 and/or https://github.com/PrismarineJS/node-minecraft-protocol/issues/176

commit.message: Make stream option optional, caller can setSocket() later
Remove stream option, since callers can simply use client.setSocket()
Add 'stream' option to client/tcp_dns, alternative to host,port for TCP
